{
  "stem": "14552.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It took a-- you know, some people may remember.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't have a memory of-- of the time span, but I would say it was a week.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No food.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And somebody got a hold of a little water and gave it to the wagons.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the Germans came and they chased them away.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but there was a little salt we had, and they would pass around the salt to everyone.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was-- that was the end.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, it was-- it was cold, and it was-- and we were trying to tell each other some things.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Whoever survives should have some information.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my mother would give her suggestions on to my sister Reggie, who she-- she knew she was not going to survive, because she was telling-- giving her directions on life and what she should do when she is not around any longer.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My mother must have known, must have had some information on the gas chambers and-- because as the way she was preparing my sister how to handle things, she must have known.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I only know that she was telling her things, but exactly what, I could not tell you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But to-- one day we came out of-- when we came out of the wagons, well, she was just talking when we came out of the wagons and when they opened the door in Auschwitz, she told my sister, she is your child now.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Take care of her.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Be a mother to her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and we hugged.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she was taken to one side and we were to another side.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's-- she didn't tell me anything to be or to do or be, or anything.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
